# 📅 Daily Plan — QAS Final Project (6 Weeks) [Updated: Jinja2 + HTMX Frontend]

> Stack: Python + Flask · PostgreSQL · Jinja2 + HTMX · Keycloak · Docker
> Pace: ~1-2 hours/day · Build on top of what you did the day before

---

## 🗓️ Week 1 — Foundation & Project Setup

**Day 1 — Repo & Structure**
- [x] Create public GitHub repo
- [ ] Set up branch strategy (main, develop, feature/*)
- [x] Add .gitignore, initial README
- [ ] Enable branch protection on main

**Day 2 — Docker Compose (base)**
- [x] Write docker-compose.yml with: Flask app, PostgreSQL
- [x] Test that both containers start and connect
- [x] Add .env file for DB credentials (no hardcoding)

**Day 3 — Flask Project Structure**
- [ ] Initialize Flask app with blueprints (products, stock, auth, reports)
- [ ] Connect SQLAlchemy to PostgreSQL
- [ ] Verify connection with a /health endpoint

**Day 4 — Database Migrations**
- [ ] Install and configure Alembic (lightweight, Python-native)
- [ ] Write first migration: create products table
- [ ] Write second migration: create stock_movements table
- [ ] Test migrations run cleanly on fresh DB

**Day 5 — Product Model & Basic CRUD**
- [ ] Implement Product model (name, SKU, description, category, price, qty, min_stock, status)
- [ ] Implement GET /products and POST /products
- [ ] Test manually with curl or Postman

**Day 6 — Complete Product CRUD**
- [ ] Implement PUT /products/:id and DELETE /products/:id
- [ ] Add pagination, search, filter, sort to GET /products
- [ ] Test all endpoints manually

**Day 7 — Rest & Catch Up**
- [ ] Review and clean up what you built this week
- [ ] Make sure Docker Compose still works end to end
- [ ] Commit everything with conventional commit messages

---

## 🗓️ Week 2 — Stock, Audit & API Docs

**Day 8 — Stock Movements**
- [ ] Implement StockMovement model (date, user, type, prev_qty, new_qty, notes)
- [ ] Implement POST /stock/movement (entry/exit)
- [ ] Auto-update product quantity on movement

**Day 9 — Stock Alerts & History**
- [ ] Implement min-stock alert logic (flag products below min_stock)
- [ ] Implement GET /stock/history with filters
- [ ] Implement GET /stock/alerts

**Day 10 — Audit Log**
- [ ] Install SQLAlchemy-Continuum or write SQLAlchemy event listeners
- [ ] Track changes on Product and StockMovement models
- [ ] Implement GET /audit endpoint

**Day 11 — OpenAPI / Swagger**
- [ ] Install flask-smorest
- [ ] Add OpenAPI decorators to all existing endpoints
- [ ] Verify Swagger UI works at /docs

**Day 12 — Reports Endpoint**
- [ ] Implement GET /reports/critical-stock
- [ ] Implement GET /reports/top-products
- [ ] Implement GET /reports/recent-movements

**Day 13 — Unit Tests (Backend)**
- [ ] Set up pytest + pytest-cov
- [ ] Write unit tests for product service (add, edit, delete, validate)
- [ ] Write unit tests for stock logic (movement, alert threshold)

**Day 14 — Rest & Catch Up**
- [ ] Run all tests, fix any failures
- [ ] Review API docs in Swagger UI
- [ ] Push everything, open a PR from develop → main

---

## 🗓️ Week 3 — Security (Keycloak)

**Day 15 — Keycloak Setup**
- [ ] Add Keycloak to Docker Compose (start-dev mode)
- [ ] Create a realm for the project
- [ ] Create a client for the Flask backend

**Day 16 — Permissions & Roles**
- [ ] Define scopes: product:view, product:manage, stock:view, stock:manage, report:view, user:manage, audit:view
- [ ] Create roles by combining scopes (not just admin/employee)
- [ ] Create test users with different roles

**Day 17 — JWT Validation in Flask**
- [ ] Install PyJWT or python-jose
- [ ] Write a JWT decode/verify middleware
- [ ] Protect all API endpoints: check token validity

**Day 18 — Permission Enforcement**
- [ ] Write a scope-checker decorator (@require_scope)
- [ ] Apply correct scope to each endpoint (not just role name)
- [ ] Test with valid and invalid tokens

**Day 19 — OAuth2 Login via Authlib**
- [ ] Install authlib
- [ ] Implement OAuth2 redirect login in Flask (/login → Keycloak → /callback)
- [ ] Store token in Flask session after callback
- [ ] Implement /logout that clears session and redirects to Keycloak logout

**Day 20 — CORS & Security Hardening**
- [ ] Configure Flask-CORS properly
- [ ] Validate all endpoints reject unauthorized requests
- [ ] Add Keycloak URLs to .env, no hardcoded secrets

**Day 21 — Rest & Catch Up**
- [ ] Test full auth flow: login → Keycloak → callback → session → protected page
- [ ] Document Keycloak setup steps in README
- [ ] Commit and open PR

---

## 🗓️ Week 4 — Frontend (Jinja2 + HTMX)

**Day 22 — Base Layout & HTMX Setup**
- [ ] Create base.html template (navbar, sidebar, flash messages)
- [ ] Add HTMX via CDN in base.html (one script tag, no install needed)
- [ ] Add TailwindCSS via CDN for styling (no build step needed)
- [ ] Create login.html that redirects to Keycloak
- [ ] Add a @login_required decorator that checks Flask session

**Day 23 — Dashboard Page**
- [ ] Create dashboard.html with cards: total products, critical stock count, recent movements, low stock alerts
- [ ] Wire cards to real data from the reports endpoints
- [ ] Add a recent movements table at the bottom

**Day 24 — Products List Page**
- [ ] Create products/index.html with a full table
- [ ] Add HTMX-powered search (hx-get on input, returns partial template)
- [ ] Add HTMX-powered pagination (hx-get on page buttons)
- [ ] Add sort by column headers

**Day 25 — Add / Edit / Delete Products**
- [ ] Create products/form.html (shared for add and edit)
- [ ] Add modal using HTMX (hx-target, hx-swap) — no JS needed
- [ ] Delete with confirmation using hx-confirm attribute
- [ ] Show success/error flash messages after each action

**Day 26 — Stock & Movement History UI**
- [ ] Create stock/update.html (entry/exit form)
- [ ] Create stock/history.html with filterable table
- [ ] Add HTMX filter by date range and movement type
- [ ] Show current stock level and alert badge if below min_stock

**Day 27 — Audit & Reports UI**
- [ ] Create audit/index.html (only rendered if session has audit:view scope)
- [ ] Create reports/index.html with critical stock and top products tables
- [ ] Hide nav links based on user scopes in base.html (Jinja2 if blocks)
- [ ] Make all pages responsive using Tailwind classes

**Day 28 — Rest & Catch Up**
- [ ] Walk through the full app as each user role
- [ ] Fix layout issues, missing data, broken links
- [ ] Commit, open PR, do code review with teammate

---

## 🗓️ Week 5 — Testing (E2E, Security, Performance)

**Day 29 — API Contract Tests**
- [ ] Install schemathesis
- [ ] Run schemathesis against your OpenAPI spec automatically
- [ ] Fix any schema mismatches found

**Day 30 — E2E Tests Setup**
- [ ] Install Playwright (Python: playwright install)
- [ ] Write E2E test: login via Keycloak, land on dashboard
- [ ] Write E2E test: add a product, verify it appears in list

**Day 31 — E2E Tests (Flows)**
- [ ] Write E2E test: stock entry/exit flow
- [ ] Write E2E test: user without audit:view scope cannot see audit page
- [ ] Add screenshot capture on every test failure

**Day 32 — Security Tests**
- [ ] Add OWASP ZAP to Docker Compose (zaproxy/zap-stable)
- [ ] Run ZAP baseline scan against staging URL
- [ ] Run pip-audit for dependency CVEs
- [ ] Document all findings even if not fixed

**Day 33 — Performance Tests**
- [ ] Install k6 (single binary, no JVM)
- [ ] Write k6 load test: GET /products (50 concurrent users)
- [ ] Write k6 stress test: POST /stock/movement
- [ ] Collect and save response time + throughput report

**Day 34 — Data & Exploratory Testing**
- [ ] Write data tests: verify migrations applied in correct order
- [ ] Test duplicate SKU constraint is enforced
- [ ] Manual exploratory testing: write 2-3 charters, log bugs found as GitHub Issues

**Day 35 — Rest & Catch Up**
- [ ] Run full test suite end to end
- [ ] Fix failing tests
- [ ] Export all test reports (HTML/XML)

---

## 🗓️ Week 6 — Observability, CI/CD & Final Polish

**Day 36 — Observability Stack**
- [ ] Add Prometheus, Grafana, Tempo, Loki, Alloy, Alertmanager to Docker Compose
- [ ] Verify all containers start cleanly

**Day 37 — Instrument Flask**
- [ ] Install opentelemetry-sdk + opentelemetry-instrumentation-flask
- [ ] Add traceId, spanId, correlationId, user, endpoint to all logs
- [ ] Instrument DB queries with OpenTelemetry
- [ ] Verify traces appear in Grafana Tempo

**Day 38 — Grafana Dashboards & Alerts**
- [ ] Create infrastructure dashboard (CPU, memory, DB pool)
- [ ] Create application dashboard (latency, throughput, error rate)
- [ ] Create business dashboard (products added, stock movements)
- [ ] Create security dashboard (auth failures, invalid tokens)
- [ ] Configure Alertmanager alerts (high CPU, high error rate, auth failures)
- [ ] Export all dashboards as JSON files

**Day 39 — GitHub Actions**
- [ ] Write .github/workflows/ci.yml
- [ ] Stages: build → unit tests → integration tests → API tests → E2E → security scan → coverage → Docker build
- [ ] Connect SonarCloud (free for public repos) to the workflow

**Day 40 — Jenkins Pipeline**
- [ ] Add Jenkins to Docker Compose
- [ ] Write Jenkinsfile with all stages matching GitHub Actions
- [ ] Verify visual pipeline runs and is green

**Day 41 — Staging Environment & Final QA**
- [ ] Write docker-compose.staging.yml replicating production
- [ ] Deploy staging and run E2E + OWASP ZAP against the live staging URL
- [ ] Fix any last issues found

**Day 42 — Documentation & Presentation**
- [ ] Write requirements document (functional & non-functional)
- [ ] Write architecture diagrams
- [ ] Write installation guide (docker compose up and you're done)
- [ ] Finalize README
- [ ] Prepare live demo for presentation
- [ ] Verify both teammates have equitable commits, PRs, and issues

